<p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Hi {{lead.First Name:default=there}},</span><br> <br><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Please join us for the webinar, <em><a href="https://content.pivotal.io/webinars/sep-28-building-event-driven-systems-with-spring-cloud-stream-webinar?utm_source=digest&amp;utm_medium=email-link&amp;utm_campaign=cqrs-springcloudstream-q317" target="_blank" id="" style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;">Building Event-Driven Systems with Spring Cloud Stream</a>,</em>&nbsp;on September 28, 2017. </span></p> 
<p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Event sourcing architectures naturally lead to messaging and CQRS-based services. We can benefit from getting rid of typical relational database models and replacing them with event reconstruction. <br><br> Join this webinar to understand how events naturally imply projections and different read models for data. In this talk we will explore these patterns, implemented with real Spring Cloud Stream applications. We will review how ES and CQRS concepts were perceived and used in the database construct for many years and what's new about them in a microservices context. <br><br>You'll also&nbsp;learn how to leverage eventual consistency and event-driven architecture with the use of pure Spring tools. For the fans of Functional Programming, you will learn how you can model your domain with just functions, pattern matching, left fold and immutability. Never lose information in your ORM-based system again! <br><br> <strong>Presenter</strong>: Jakub Pillmon, Software Developer / Trainer / Architect</span></p> 
<p><span style="font-family: helvetica; font-size: 14px;"><strong>Date</strong>: Thursday, September&nbsp;28, 2017<br><strong>Time</strong>: 10:00am PDT / 1:00pm EDT</span></p> 
